   Sunday at Royce Hall, the American Youth Symphony has added local composer Leon Levitch's Elegy for Strings -- a personal choice from conductor Mehli Mehta -- to the program to honor Bernstein, who died last Sunday. Last Monday, KUSC-FM (91.5) devoted its entire day of live broadcasting, from 6 a.m. to 10 p.m., to performances -- as conductor and pianist -- and compositions of Bernstein, including an unusual recording from 1956 of him discussing Beethoven's Fifth Symphony .
